Ingredients

125g  Butter (at room temperature)
125g  caster sugar
2     eggs (not straight from fridge)
125g  plain flour
3/4 tspn  baking powder
Some  Milk
3 tbspn  cocoa powder

Steps

1 - Mix the butter and sugar into a pasty mess
2 - Crack in the eggs and beat into a slightly gooey pasty mess
3 - Sieve flour and baking powder together. Add to wet ingredients in thirds and fold in after each addition
4 - Sieve cocoa powder into wet mix and fold all together
5 - Add a little milk until it has a custard-like consistency
6 - Grease a cake tin and line with thing to stop the cake sticking (baking parchment)
7 - Pour cake batter into tin
8 - Cook at 180 degrees C for about 20mins
9 - Place on a rack to cool
10 - Eat
11 - Icing, optional
